observations.recommendation:
We recommended the following in which the Management agreed to undertake:

a. Ensure that all cash advances shall be fully liquidated at the end of each year. Unused cash advances for the year should be returned or refunded to the collecting officer at year-end;
b. Issued demand letters to all active employees whose cash advances were still not liquidated. Otherwise, request settlement of the accounts;
c. Conduct regular monitoring and analysis of long outstanding cash advances and may start the process of writing off the accounts by requesting to the auditors based on the COA Circular 2016-005;
d. Ensure that cash advances shall only be given for a legally authorized specific purpose and adequately supported with relevant supporting documents;
e. Revisit the provisions on supporting documents on the grants and liquidations of cash advances and strictly adhere thereto; and
f. Stop granting additional cash advances to officials and employees until the previous ones have been liquidated and/or settled.

We recommended that:

a. The Municipal Agriculture Office require the recipients of the CFAD projects to submit the necessary documents needed for liquidation;
b. The Municipal Accounting Office submit timely the liquidation reports of the funds pertaining to completed projects and ensure that excess funds from these projects are returned to the source agencies.

We recommended and Management agreed on the following:
a. Direct the Municipal General Services Officer to locate documents pertinent to the LGU properties preparatory to the conduct of the mandatory physical inventory;
b. Create an inventory team to conduct a complete physical count / inventory of all properties in accordance with existing regulations and in order to establish the actual existence;
c. Submit a complete Report on the Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment (RPCPPE) and Inventory and Inspection Report of Unserviceable Property (IIRUP) to the Accounting Office for reconciliation with the latter's ledger cards;
d. Require the GSO to maintain property cards as control records to facilitate the regular reconciliation of records with MAO; and
e. Make appropriate and necessary adjustments in the books of accounts.

We recommended and Management agreed on the following:
a. Direct the Municipal Accountant to follow the proper accounting entries in the transfer of unexpended DRRMF;
b. Direct the Municipal Accountant to abide with the provisions of COA Circular No. 2012-002 in maintaining subsidiary ledger on a by year and by source basis for the DRRM special trust fund account;
c. Direct the Municipal Budget Officer to abide with the guidelines provided by COA Circular 2012-002 especially on the inclusion of unexpended/unobligated LDRRMF for Capital Outlay in the continuing appropriation of General Fund books.

We recommended and Management agreed on the following:
a. Return to the Source Agency the amount received for which the intended purpose could no longer be pursued and the unused balances of completed projects;
b. Proper turnover of documents and tasks in case of employee separation to ensure continuity of project implementation;
c. Prompt preparation and availability of project designs to make certain the implementation / execution of the projects; and
d. Monitor and implement timely the programs, projects and activities entrusted to the LGU.

