We recommended and Management agreed on the following:
Direct the Municipal General Services Officer to locate documents pertinent to the LGU properties preparatory to the conduct of the mandatory physical inventory;
Create an inventory team to conduct a complete physical count / inventory of all properties in accordance with existing regulations and in order to establish the actual existence;
Submit a complete Report on the Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment (RPCPPE) and Inventory and Inspection Report of Unserviceable Property (IIRUP) to the Accounting Office for reconciliation with the latter's ledger cards;
Require the GSO to maintain property cards as control records to facilitate the regular reconciliation of records with MAO; and
Make appropriate and necessary adjustments in the books of accounts.

We recommended and Management agreed on the following:
Direct the Municipal Accountant to follow the proper accounting entries in the transfer of unexpended DRRMF;
Direct the Municipal Accountant to abide with the provisions of COA Circular No. 2012-002 in maintaining subsidiary ledger on a by year and by source basis for the DRRM special trust fund account;
Direct the Municipal Budget Officer to abide with the guidelines provided by COA Circular 2012-002 especially on the inclusion of unexpended/unobligated LDRRMF for Capital Outlay in the continuing appropriation of General Fund books.

In view of the above-mentioned audit observations, we recommended and Management agreed on the following:
Return to the Source Agency the amount received for which the intended purpose could no longer be pursued and the unused balances of completed projects;
Proper turnover of documents and tasks in case of employee separation to ensure continuity of project implementation;
Prompt preparation and availability of project designs to make certain the implementation / execution of the projects; and
Monitor and implement timely the programs, projects and activities entrusted to the LGU.
